-- Santander says to issue $2.5 bln in convertible preference shares 
-- By Paul Day
-- Thu May 08, 2014 02:26AM EDT
-- None



MADRID, May 8 (Reuters) - Spain's largest bank Santander <SAN.MC> said on Thursday it plans to issue $2.5 billion in preference shares, convertible to normal shares, to institutional investors in an accelerated book building process.

